<h2>The Edwin Banks Memorial Fund</h2>

<p>The Edwin Banks Memorial Fund was established by Dr. Banks' wife, Mrs. Hilda Banks, and family to honor his long and distinguished career as a faculty member in the Department of Ecology, Ethology and Evolution (now the Department of Animal Biology) at the University of Illinois (1957-1985).
Dr. Banks was a pre-eminent researcher in the areas of mammalian sociality and reproduction.</p>

<p><strong>Purpose:</strong> To support graduate student research in animal behavior.
One research award of $800 will be awarded following a positive evaluation by the Graduate Programs Committee.</p>

<p><strong>Eligibility:</strong> Any graduate student in the Department of Animal Biology studying any aspect of behavior may apply.</p>

<p><strong>Application:</strong> To apply, please submit one copy of each of the following:</p>

<ol>
<li>A proposal describing the research to be conducted.
The proposal should not exceed two-double spaced pages.</li>
<li>A current C.V.</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Closing Date:</strong> TBA, see Department of Animal Biology</p>

